    • Method Detail

      • setFailedOcspJobsRetryInterval

        public ALBOCSPConfig.Builder setFailedOcspJobsRetryInterval(java.lang.Long failedOcspJobsRetryInterval)
        Describes the Time Interval after which the next OCSP job needs to be scheduled in case of the OCSP job failures. Allowed values are 60-86400. Unit is SEC. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as 3600. format: int64
        Parameters:
        failedOcspJobsRetryInterval - New value for the property.

      • setMaxTries

        public ALBOCSPConfig.Builder setMaxTries(java.lang.Long maxTries)
        Maximum number of times the failed OCSP jobs can be scheduled. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as 10. format: int64
        Parameters:
        maxTries - New value for the property.

      • setOcspReqInterval

        public ALBOCSPConfig.Builder setOcspReqInterval(java.lang.Long ocspReqInterval)
        Interval between the OCSP queries. Allowed values are 60-31536000. Unit is SEC. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as 86400. format: int64
        Parameters:
        ocspReqInterval - New value for the property.

      • setOcspRespTimeout

        public ALBOCSPConfig.Builder setOcspRespTimeout(java.lang.Long ocspRespTimeout)
        Time in seconds that the system waits for a reply from the OCSP responder before dropping the connection. Unit is SEC. format: int64
        Parameters:
        ocspRespTimeout - New value for the property.

      • setResponderUrlLists

        public ALBOCSPConfig.Builder setResponderUrlLists(java.util.List<java.lang.String> responderUrlLists)
        List of Responder URLs configured by user to do failover/override the AIA extension contained in the OCSP responder's SSL/TLS certificate.
        Parameters:
        responderUrlLists - New value for the property.

      • setUrlAction

        public ALBOCSPConfig.Builder setUrlAction(java.lang.String urlAction)
        Possible values are:
        • ALBOCSPConfig.URL_ACTION_FAILOVER
        • ALBOCSPConfig.URL_ACTION_OVERRIDE
        Describes the type of action to take with the Responder URLs. Enum options - OCSP_RESPONDER_URL_FAILOVER, OCSP_RESPONDER_URL_OVERRIDE. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as OCSP_RESPONDER_URL_FAILOVER.
        Parameters:
        urlAction - New value for the property.
